discussion.content:
Looks like D is the right option. 
https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/mt/customizing-account-configuration-aws-control-tower-lifecycle-events/ 
Above link shows that we can modify the security groups using firewall manager via factory template. On the other hand, you can configure SCP for an OU to deny modifications for a security group. Go to Org ==> rules ==> SCP ==> create 
{
 "Version": "2012-10-17",
 "Statement": [
 {
 "Sid": "Statement1",
 "Effect": "Deny",
 "Action": [
 "ec2:CreateSecurityGroup",
 "ec2:DeleteSecurityGroup",
 "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroupReferences",
 "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroupRules",
 "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups",
 "ec2:ModifySecurityGroupRules"
 ],
 "Resource": [
 "*"
 ]
 }
 ]
}
